Cryptoart is an artistic subgenre that emerged in 2016 out of the crypto world, where it has become a prominent sub-category within the larger genre of crypto-anarchy. These artists use the tools and the mediums of contemporary digital culture, specifically the internet, to create images of what would otherwise be considered impossible, even for a very artistic mind.

It is difficult to classify this form of art, so we are taking a look at the elements that help create such artworks. The tools, mediums and mediums used are a part of the crypto-anarchy world.
